text:
Celebrations, Parades and Municipal Events: A contingent of girls in the 1894 Decoration Day Parade. Buildings in the background are on the west side of Broadway, at 26th Street.

May 30, 1894.

The Illustrated American
title: Celebrations - Parades - Municipal events - Decoration Day Parade.

text:
Broadway, south from 26th Street. Fifth Avenue is to the left and intersects this thoroughfare at 23rd Street. The apex formed at that point is occupied by the triangular Fuller (Flat-iron) Building. To the left appears the low white structure that was the former Hotel Bartholdi: View 2 is photographed from 25th Street, being closer to the aforementioned features. The street clock is in front of the 5th Avenue Building.
